## Payments DB — tables QA uses most

**Separate database named `Payments`** on the same STAGE server (verified table list 2026-07-16 in `docs/guides/stage-sql-schema-verified.md`). PM API txn ids (ULID `01K…`) are here — not Platform / not master.

Schemas present: `AccountUpdater`, `Fees`, `Payments`, `Returns`, `Transactions`.

| Schema.Table | Use |
|--------------|-----|
| `[AccountUpdater].[ReturnDeactivations]` | Hard-return deactivation — `WellfitTokenId`, `OriginalPaymentId`, `ProcessorTransactionId`, `ReturnCode`, `Status`, resolve fields (Payments DB only; full cols in schema-verified) |
| `[AccountUpdater].[AchNOCs]` | NOC claim/ingest |
| `[AccountUpdater].[UnmatchedAchNOCs]` | Unmatched NOCs |
| `[AccountUpdater].[TokenMigrationFiles]`, `[TokenMigrationRecords]` | Token migration |
| `[Transactions].[PaymentTransaction]` | PM payment txn — **Payments DB only**. API id = col **`PaymentTransactionId`** (nvarchar ULID). PK **`Id`** = GUID. Status = **`TransactionStatusId`**. |
| `[Transactions].[PaymentMethodACH]` | ACH method. Join: **`PaymentMethodACH.PaymentTransactionId` (GUID) = `PaymentTransaction.Id`**. Cols include RoutingNumber, MaskedAccountNumber. |
| `[Transactions].[PaymentTransactionHistory]` | Status history |
| `[Transactions].[TransactionStatus]` | Status lookup — full Id/Code map in `docs/guides/stage-sql-schema-verified.md` (6=SETTLED, 10=REFUNDED, 18=PARTIALLY_REFUNDED, …) |
| `[Transactions].[TransactionType]` | 1=DEBIT, 2=CREDIT, 5=REFUND, 6=VOID, … (see schema-verified) |
| `[Transactions].[Rail]` | 1=ACH, 2=CNP, 3=CP |
| `[Transactions].[OriginType]` | WEB/TEL/PPD/CCD (ACH 1–4); ECOM/MOTO (CNP 5–6); POS/TAP_TO_PAY (CP 7–8) — see schema-verified |
| `[Transactions].[ACHReturn]` | PM ACH return — `PaymentTransactionId`→`PaymentTransaction.Id`, reason codes, retry fields (see schema-verified) |
| `[Transactions].[ACHNotificationOfChange]` | PM NOC — `NocCode`, original/corrected routing-account-name, `IsProcessed` (full cols in schema-verified) |
| `[Returns].[RedepositAttempts]` | Redeposit attempts — `ReturnedPaymentId`, `OriginalPaymentId`, `AttemptNumber`, `RedepositPaymentId`, `AttemptStatus`, … |
| `[Returns].[ReturnConfigurations]` | Per-merchant redeposit config — `SubMerchantId`, `ProcessorId`, `MaxRedepositAttempts` |
| `[Payments].[PaymentRequests]`, `[AchDailyCounter]`, `[AchLimitEnforcementAuditLog]` | Requests / ACH limits (Payments DB) |

